  
                    
                        
                
                
            British Olympic sprinter Nigel Levine has been banned from all sport for four years after failing a drugs test.The European indoor gold medallist was provisionally suspended in February after he reportedly tested positive for banned asthma drug clenbuterol. And UK Anti-Doping have now confirmed the 29-year-old's ban. 
    
        
Levine was part of Britain's 4x400m team that competed at the 2016 Rio Olympics.More to follow.
 
